comment: Turned out a it darker than I expected. I am a dark fan, but this is much more copped/brown than light. Ah well. Maybe the LHBS made a slight error in the mix of grains. I got about 1.055 on a 5.5 gal batch. Made a yeast starter 2 days ago with dark Belgian DME and pitched this morning. I am excited to see how the Mangrovejack compares to the WL British 07.
